abstract="PURPOSE: Understanding test-retest variability (TRV) of mesopic microperimetry is  critical for defining meaningful treatment effects in retinitis pigmentosa (RP)  trials. This study uniquely evaluates intra- and intervisit TRV and coefficients  of repeatability (CoRs) for microperimetry parameters in RP patients with varying  best-corrected visual acuity (BCVA) levels. METHODS: In this single-centre  prospective cohort study, RP patients were assessed on two visits, 14.0{\thinspace}days  apart. Patients were grouped by BCVA: low (≤20/50 Snellen; ≥0.4{\thinspace}logMAR) or  moderate (>20/50 Snellen; <0.4{\thinspace}logMAR). Using Bland-Altman analyses, the CoRs for  intra- and intervisit variability were determined for pointwise (dB), mean (dB),  and volume sensitivity (dB*deg(2)) on mesopic microperimetry. RESULTS: Intravisit  CoRs for mean, volume, and pointwise sensitivity were 1.7{\thinspace}dB, 353.2{\thinspace}dB*deg(2),  and 8.6{\thinspace}dB, respectively, in the low-BCVA group (n{\thinspace}={\thinspace}32), and 0.9{\thinspace}dB,  254.5{\thinspace}dB*deg(2), and 7.3{\thinspace}dB in the moderate-BCVA group (n{\thinspace}={\thinspace}15). Intervisit CoRs  for mean, volume, and pointwise sensitivity were 2.4{\thinspace}dB, 355.2{\thinspace}dB*deg(2), and  10.2{\thinspace}dB in the low-BCVA group (n{\thinspace}={\thinspace}31). The moderate-BCVA group (n{\thinspace}={\thinspace}16) showed  smaller CoRs of 1.6{\thinspace}dB, 386.8{\thinspace}dB*deg(2), and 7.7{\thinspace}dB for mean, volume, and  pointwise sensitivity. BCVA and mean sensitivity, but not fixation stability, are  predictors of TRV for volume sensitivity. CONCLUSIONS: Due to significant TRV,  pointwise sensitivity is an unreliable endpoint for RP patients, irrespective of  BCVA. Mean sensitivity is suitable as an endpoint when BCVA is relatively  preserved. Volume sensitivity provides additional spatial information, and shows  promise as a clinical endpoint for assessing macular sensitivity changes on  mesopic microperimetry in patients with RP.",
