abstract="PURPOSE: To survey the clinical responses to treatment of chronic postoperative  and uveitic cystoid macular edema (CME) with a dexamethasone-based intravitreal  implant (Ozurdex(®)). METHODS: This retrospective, interventional case series  reports on patients with chronic CME after uncomplicated vitrectomy for  epiretinal gliosis or phacoemulsification (group 1: 12 eyes) or secondary to  noninfectious endogenous uveitis (group 2: 36 eyes). Central retinal thickness  (CRT), best-corrected visual acuity (BCVA, logMAR), and intraocular pressure  (IOP) throughout follow-up were gleaned from the medical records. RESULTS: In  group 1, CRT decreased, compared with baseline, from 519{\thinspace}{\textpm}{\thinspace}43 to 297{\thinspace}{\textpm}{\thinspace}23 and  356{\thinspace}{\textpm}{\thinspace}49{\thinspace}$\mu$m by the 1- and 3-month visit (P{\thinspace}={\thinspace}0.02) and to 429{\thinspace}{\textpm}{\thinspace}57{\thinspace}$\mu$m before  reimplantation. In group 2, CRT decreased from 460{\thinspace}{\textpm}{\thinspace}31 to 300{\thinspace}{\textpm}{\thinspace}21 and  312{\thinspace}{\textpm}{\thinspace}26{\thinspace}$\mu$m by the 1- and 3-month follow-up, respectively (P{\thinspace}={\thinspace}0.001), and to  373{\thinspace}{\textpm}{\thinspace}32{\thinspace}$\mu$m before reimplantation. Complete resolution of CME was achieved in 67{\%}  and 94{\%} (groups 1 and 2, respectively) by 1 month and in 42{\%} and 80{\%} by 3 months  after injection. In group 1, BCVA improved from 0.46{\thinspace}{\textpm}{\thinspace}0.08 to 0.27{\thinspace}{\textpm}{\thinspace}0.09 and  0.20{\thinspace}{\textpm}{\thinspace}0.06 (P{\thinspace}={\thinspace}0.01) by the 1- and 3-month follow-up, respectively, and to  0.32{\thinspace}{\textpm}{\thinspace}0.08 before reimplantation. In group 2, BCVA improved from 0.47{\thinspace}{\textpm}{\thinspace}0.06 to  0.34{\thinspace}{\textpm}{\thinspace}0.09, 0.26{\thinspace}{\textpm}{\thinspace}0.07, and 0.29{\thinspace}{\textpm}{\thinspace}0.08 (P{\thinspace}<{\thinspace}0.05) at 1 and 3 months of  follow-up and before reimplantation, respectively. A significant IOP increase was  not observed in either group. Mean time to reimplantation of Ozurdex was  6.4{\thinspace}{\textpm}{\thinspace}5.7 and 6.6{\thinspace}{\textpm}{\thinspace}3.4 months for postoperative and uveitic CME, respectively.  CONCLUSION: Ozurdex seems to achieve a sustained effect over up to 6 months in  postsurgical and uveitic CME.",
